org.apache.flink.core.fs

类 SafetyNetCloseableRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.util.AbstractCloseableRegistry<WrappingProxyCloseable<? extends java.io.Closeable>,SafetyNetCloseableRegistry.PhantomDelegatingCloseableRef>
      • org.apache.flink.core.fs.SafetyNetCloseableRegistry
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    @Internal
public class SafetyNetCloseableRegistry
extends AbstractCloseableRegistry<WrappingProxyCloseable<? extends java.io.Closeable>,SafetyNetCloseableRegistry.PhantomDelegatingCloseableRef>
    This implementation of an AbstractCloseableRegistry registers WrappingProxyCloseable. When the proxy becomes subject to GC, this registry takes care of closing unclosed Closeables.

    Phantom references are used to track when WrappingProxys of Closeable got GC'ed. We ensure that the wrapped Closeable is properly closed to avoid resource leaks.

    Other than that, it works like a normal CloseableRegistry.

    All methods in this class are thread-safe.
